      "text": "1. User Dashboard Layout & Navigation\n\nCreate a dedicated UserDashboard page/component.\nAdd a user-friendly navbar (profile, orders, logout, etc.).\nInclude a search bar and filters (by city, cuisine, rating, etc.).\n2. Fetch & Display Shops\n\nOn dashboard load, fetch all available shops from your backend.\nDisplay shops in a grid or list with key info: name, image, address, rating, cuisine.\nAllow users to filter/sort shops (by location, cuisine, popularity).\n3. Shop Details & Menu\n\nWhen a user clicks a shop, show a detailed shop page:\nShop info (name, image, address, description, rating).\nList of menu items (with image, name, price, type, category).\nOption to view reviews/ratings.\n4. Add to Cart & Ordering\n\nAllow users to add menu items to their cart.\nShow a cart summary (items, quantity, total price).\nImplement checkout flow (address, payment, order confirmation).\n5. User Profile & Orders\n\nAdd a profile section (view/edit user info).\nShow past orders and order status.\nAllow users to reorder or review items/shops.\n6. Location & Personalization\n\nUse geolocation to show nearby shops.\nPersonalize recommendations based on user history or preferences.\n7. Responsive & Modern UI\n\nEnsure the dashboard is mobile-friendly.\nUse modern UI components (cards, modals, toasts).\n8. Error Handling & Loading States\n\nShow loading spinners while fetching data.\nDisplay clear error messages for failed requests.\n9. Security & Access Control\n\nEnsure only authenticated users can access the dashboard.\nProtect user data and order info.\n10. Optional Features\n\nAdd ratings/reviews for shops and items.\nImplement favorite shops/items.\nAdd notifications for order status.\nHow to Start:\n\nBegin with the dashboard layout and shop listing.\nIntegrate backend APIs for fetching shops and items.\nBuild shop detail and menu views.\nAdd cart and order functionality.\nExpand with profile, orders, and personalization features.\n",
